    "body": "It's not really the lengths that matter, rather the labels are *aligned* to match. I'd recommend you read through [the docs on this](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/basics.html#reindexing-and-altering-labels). since `df_b` is a subset of `df_a` it looks like it's the lengths.\r\n\r\nI don't understand what your second point means. An operation between two valid values will be valid. An operation between any value and `nan` will be `nan`.\r\n"
